title: Fast Continuous Wavelet Transform
text: basic example shows invoke fcwt library calculate continuous wavelet transform plot result. helpers conveniently convert matrix meaningful data frame: can also directly plot resulting scalogram:
code: library(fcwtr)  # You are given some signal encoded in a numeric vector. # In this example we use some superimposed sin signals. signal <- ts_sin_superpos  # One possibility is to use the fcwt library (almost) directly through # a thin wrapper: output <-   fcwt(     signal,     sample_freq = 44100,     freq_begin = 16,     freq_end = 2100,     n_freqs = 200,     sigma = 5   )  # In this case the result is a matrix, # which can be used for further processing. dim(output) #> [1] 6000  200 as.data.frame(output) |> head(10) #>    time_ind freq value         time #> 1         0 2100    NA 0.000000e+00 #> 2         1 2100    NA 2.267574e-05 #> 3         2 2100    NA 4.535147e-05 #> 4         3 2100    NA 6.802721e-05 #> 5         4 2100    NA 9.070295e-05 #> 6         5 2100    NA 1.133787e-04 #> 7         6 2100    NA 1.360544e-04 #> 8         7 2100    NA 1.587302e-04 #> 9         8 2100    NA 1.814059e-04 #> 10        9 2100    NA 2.040816e-04 plot(output)

title: Performs a fast continuous wavelet transform. — fcwt
text: signal Real-valued time series. time step gaps assumed uniform. sample_freq Sampling rate input time series physical units. freq_begin Sets minimal frequency (> 0!), units sample_freq, contained output. freq_end Sets maximal frequency (> freq_begin!), units sample_freq, contained output. n_freqs Number frequency bins generated CWT. frequencies linearly distributed. Computation time increases raising number frequency bins. sigma Sets dimensionless parameter modifying wavelet spread time-domain roughly given \(\Sigma_t \sim \sqrt{2} \frac{\sigma}{f}\). Changing parameter adjusts time/frequency uncertainty balance. Defaults 1. Larger (lower) value sigma corresponds better (worse) frequency resolution worse (better) time resolution. remove_coi Boundary effects can result nonphysical artifacts. Remove settings corresponding values NA. define essential support (Gaußian) wavelet four times standard deviation, \(4 \Sigma_t = 2 * \sqrt{2} \frac{\sigma}{f}\), wavelet touches boundary distance center wavelet boundary less \(4 \Sigma_t\). Values fall range removed `remove_coi = TRUE`. nthreads Number threads used computation, applicable.

title: Performs a fast continuous wavelet transform. — fcwt
text: numeric real-valued matrix dim = c(length(signal), n_freqs).

title: FCWT on long sequences — fcwt_batch
text: Performs fast continuous wavelet transform long sequences. used short sequences, since boundary artefacts discarded, potentially dominate short sequences.

title: FCWT on long sequences — fcwt_batch
code: fcwt_batch(   signal,   sample_freq,   freq_begin,   freq_end,   n_freqs,   sigma,   max_batch_size = ceiling(4 * 10^9/(n_freqs * 4)),   time_resolution,   nthreads = 8L )

title: FCWT on long sequences — fcwt_batch
text: signal Real-valued time series. time step gaps assumed uniform. sample_freq Sampling rate input time series physical units. freq_begin Sets minimal frequency (> 0!), units sample_freq, contained output. freq_end Sets maximal frequency (> freq_begin!), units sample_freq, contained output. n_freqs Number frequency bins generated CWT. frequencies linearly distributed. Computation time increases raising number frequency bins. sigma Sets dimensionless parameter modifying wavelet spread time-domain roughly given \(\Sigma_t \sim \sqrt{2} \frac{\sigma}{f}\). Changing parameter adjusts time/frequency uncertainty balance. Defaults 1. Larger (lower) value sigma corresponds better (worse) frequency resolution worse (better) time resolution. max_batch_size maximal batch size used splitting input sequence. limits maximal memory used. Defaults roughly 4GB. actual batch size optimized use FFTW. time_resolution time resolution inverse units `sample_freq` result. Memory consumption directly related . Can higher time resolution input signal. nthreads Number threads used computation, applicable.

title: FCWT on long sequences — fcwt_batch
text: case input sequences exceed certain size, outputl sequence fit local memory fcwt performed one run. instance, case processing song 10 minutes length (assuming sampling rate 44100 Hz), size output vector `10 * 60 seconds * 44100 Hz * nfreqs * 4 bytes`, e.g. `nfreqs = 200`, equals ~ 21 GB, hence nowadays already limit hardware modern personal computer. cases needed output time-resolution smaller time resolution input signal, one can perform fcwt reduce output size averaging. (input signal time resolution can general reduced since high-frequency information get lost.) function splits input sequence batches, processes batch separately, reduces time resolution, adds outputs together. Attention: Boundary artefacts removed, high frequency information beginning end sequence lost. (amount depends minimal frequency captured `min_freq`.)
